<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="346" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Herdliska</persName>
                                    to Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-09"><hi rend="italic">August 9,
                                        1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 118.]</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                                receipt this morning of Acting Secretary Adee’s open telegram of
                                yesterday’s date, reading as follows:<note n="1" xml:id="d346fn1">Printed ante.</note></p>
                            <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                            <p>Immediately upon receipt of the above cablegram I called upon Count
                                Szecsen, in the absence of Count Goluchowski on leave. Imperial and
                                royal acting minister for foreign affairs, and communicated the
                                contents thereof to him, handing him at the same time a copy. Count
                                Szecsen expressed his thanks for the communication and assured me
                                that the information imparted and the attitude taken by the United
                                States would be received with great satisfaction by the Imperial and
                                Royal Government.</p>
                            <p>I have the honor to be, etc.,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles V. Herdliska</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Chargé</hi>.</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>